void set_standard_block(int ibBlock, int iTicks, string sEffectId,
  string sStart, string sStop)

  An lfun that will set the standard blocks we use on the mud.
  See /open/INCLUDE/blocks.h for the list. You must #include <blocks.h>
  when using set_standard_block.

  ibBlock is the block or blocks you are setting (eg BLK_BLIND|BLK_PARALYZE).
  iTicks is the number of seconds the block will be set (the function
    will round up to the next multiple of 2).
  sEffectId is the unique name of your effect. Without a unique name,
    you run the risk of the default id being overwritten by other
    effects without names as well.
  sStart and sStop are messages relayed to the object having the block
    set, and to the room. If the string doesn't end with \n, the function
    will add it. If either/both are not set, the function will use the
    default messages (eg. You have been blinded. / You are no longer blind.).

  Example:
    oTarget->set_standard_block(BLK_PARALYZE|BLK_BLIND, 2,
      "test_block_id","$N $vpoke $no in the eye, before throwing \
out $p back.","$N $vrecover from $p self-inflicted ordeal.");

** Note: if you have more than one block set, sStop will be
         used for each block.
